		<part id="api-business">
			<title>API Business Value</title>
			<slide id="collaboration">
				<title>API Value #1: Collaboration</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Teams collaborate <em>through APIs</em></li>
					<ul>
						<li>Value is exposed <em>through APIs for others to use</em></li>
						<li>Value is consumed <em>through APIs for loose coupling</em></li>
					</ul>
					<li>Teams <em>always</em> produce building blocks for others to use</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="innovation">
				<title>API Value #2: Innovation</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Innovation needs collaboration and autonomy</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Collaboration</em> becomes easier with loosely coupled APIs</li>
						<li>Upfront investments become smaller because APIs are readily available</li>
					</ul>
					<li>The available <q>solution space</q> becomes bigger</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="co-creation">
				<title>API Value #3: Co-Creation</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Collaborating <em>with partners</em> becomes a natural thing to do</li>
					<li>Replace <em>integration</em> with <em>reusable interconnection</em> for better scale</li>
					<li>Business side must embrace business models based on business platforms</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="working">
			<title>Getting APIs to Work</title>
			<slide id="open-platform">
				<title>Precondition #1: Open Platform</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Building an open platform allows everybody to participate</li>
					<li>Maintaining/evolving it is more effort than building it</li>
					<li>Focus on creating value on the platform instead of building it</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="valuable-apis">
				<title>Precondition #2: Valuable APIs</title>
				<ul>
					<li>APIs only create value when they are used</li>
					<li>Business-aligned APIs are needed to create <link href="api-business"/></li>
					<li><em>Everybody</em> (tech/business) must understand how APIs (can) create value</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="ecosystem">
				<title>Precondition #3: Ecosystem Spirit</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Moving from <q>building a product</q> to <q>contributing a building block</q></li>
					<li>No product is perfect, every product can be improved, so let's make that easy</li>
					<li>Switching from <q>building systems</q> to <q>evolving ecosystems</q> can be challenging</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
